Check if you’re washing your hands well
We all know that they need to be washed (e.g. after coming home or before a meal).
But not everyone knows that in order to actually get rid of germs, you have to do it in the right way.
This is especially important now that autumn infections are approaching.
It takes at least 30-40 seconds to remove dangerous bacteria and viruses from our hands to a sufficient degree.
Most of us wash them shorter!
It is enough to have hot water and ordinary soap – it is not true that it must be antibacterial (many doctors even advise against it).
Washing, we rub not only the bottoms and tops of the hand, but also: finger tips (connected or individually) – rub them with circular movements against the interior of the other hand, the spaces between your fingers (weave your hands, rubbing your fingers on yourself), thumbs – each thumb includes the other hand and in such a way we turn to the right and left with it.
In an emergency situation (when it is impossible to wash our hands) wet hands with a wet tissue, and then use antibacterial gel (in drugstores, from 5 PLN).
After using the public toilet, do not touch with washed handles or doors (recommendation of the Chief Sanitary Inspectorate).
Open it through a paper towel.
Iranian President Says He has rejected a proposal for talks with the US, Donald Trump denies
Tehran has not entered into talks with the U.S. side at the United Nations General Assembly in New York, despite an offer to lift sanctions by the Americans, Iranian President Hassan Rouhani said on Friday.
U.S. President Donald Trump commented that it was the Iranian side who asked for the lifting of the restrictions, which he did not agree to.
According to Iranian President Hassan Rouhani, the Americans have proposed lifting all sanctions imposed on Tehran in exchange for negotiations on a new international agreement.
It would regulate both Iran’s nuclear program and the ballistic missile program.
Rouhani: Iran will not engage in a maximum pressure atmosphere
Iran's president said he had not agreed to take up these talks because of the “toxic atmosphere.”
He said he met with U.S. diplomats because he succumbed to France, Germany and the United Kingdom.
However, he stressed that Iran would not engage in talks in an atmosphere of “maximum pressure.”
“Even if we want to negotiate with the Americans in 5+1 format, no one can predict what the end result will be,” Rouhani said.
The day before, the Iranian leader said it did not rule out talks with the United States, and the European parties accused the European parties of the nuclear deal favoring US sanctions on Iran.
He added that sanctions imposed on Iran after the U.S. withdrawal from the nuclear deal “are a prerequisite that does not allow” to establish a dialogue.
If we can abolish this precondition and if America lifts sanctions and maximum pressure, then of course we can talk to America.
He added that he did not rule out a meeting with US President Donald Trump, even though he did not agree to such an interview in the past week at the UN General Assembly.
Trump: “Iran asked, I said no.”
Donald Trump tweeted that he had rejected the request of the Iranian side.
“Iran wanted me to lift the sanctions imposed on them so that we could meet.
Of course, I said ‘no!’ tweeted the President of the United States.
Tension with the nuclear agreement in the background
France, Germany and the United Kingdom are trying to ease tensions between Washington and Tehran to save the 2015 Iran deal they were signatories in some form.
It stipulated that in exchange for lifting economic sanctions, Iran would abandon its nuclear weapons program, and the nuclear sector would be in control of the International Atomic Energy Agency (IAEA).
Since the U.S. withdrawal from the deal in May 2015, the remaining signatories have repeatedly confirmed that they want to keep the agreement in force.
Nothing came of it so far.
Washington is using the tactic of exerting maximum pressure on Iran, and the sanctions also include a full embargo on Iranian oil.
Tehran has said that if it does not receive a permit to export the raw material, it will limit its obligations under the agreement every 60 days.
