He came high, he fell low
Marian Banaś is the new president of the Supreme Audit Office.
He was appointed to this position on 30 August 2019, for a six-year term.
His candidacy was submitted by Law and Justice and accepted by the party’s politicians.
Previously, Banaś was associated with NIK from 1992 to 2005, he acted in this institution as a collaborator of Lech Kaczyński.
During the first PiS government (2005–2008), Banaś held the position of the President of the Customs Service, as well as the Undersecretary of State in the Ministry of Finance.
Since 2015, he has again sat on the stool of the head of the Customs Service, and since 2017 he has been managing the National Revenue Administration.
Banaś served as finance minister in the government of Mateusz Morawiecki for three months.
